# Repo layer boundaries

Canonical map: [`docs/SOP/REPO_LAYER_MAP_V1.md`](docs/SOP/REPO_LAYER_MAP_V1.md)  
Path presets: [`docs/SOP/REPO_LAYER_PATH_PREFIXES.json`](docs/SOP/REPO_LAYER_PATH_PREFIXES.json)

## Before you edit

1. Identify **layer**: `msos-shell` | `ppe-ui` | `ppe-core` | `dev-factory` | `platform` | `product-canon`
2. If a BUILD packet or sprint lists `LAYER_PRESET` / `ALLOWED_PATHS`, **stay inside them**
3. Declare **plane** per [`OPERATING_RULES.md`](docs/SOP/OPERATING_RULES.md) — do not mix planes in one pass

## Hard rules

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **No TS/math port** | `apps/msos-web/` displays PPE outputs; never reimplement distributions, disagreement, or verification in TypeScript |
| **No viz in core** | `src/engine/`, `src/data/`, `src/models/` must not import `src/viz/` |
| **No cross-runtime imports** | Next app does not import Python `src/` |
| **Thin `app.py`** | New PPE UI → new module under `src/viz/`, not a monolithic `app.py` |
| **MSOS ≠ PPE whole product** | MSOS wraps/exposes PPE; PPE remains first Strategy Lab tool ([`MSOS_WEBSITE_PROGRAM.md`](docs/SOP/MSOS_WEBSITE_PROGRAM.md)) |
| **MSOS owns shell** | Workflow, state, identity/user scope, thesis/expression lifecycle, monitor/history, entitlement display, UX around PPE |
| **PPE owns math** | Implied distributions, disagreement, evaluation/freeze outputs — Python only |
| **Native integration surface** | MSOS embeds/renders/displays PPE via stable output contract ([`MSOS_PRODUCT_BACKPLANE_CHARTER_V1.md`](docs/SOP/MSOS_PRODUCT_BACKPLANE_CHARTER_V1.md)); Streamlit may remain compute source |
| **No duplicate math** | MSOS must not reimplement PPE math in TypeScript — display/proxy/read only |

## Where to put work

| Work | Path |
|------|------|
| Homepage / platform chrome | `apps/msos-web/` (when chartered) |
| Streamlit implied lab | `src/viz/` |
| Math / fetchers | `src/engine/`, `src/data/`, `src/models/` |
| Relay / queue / SOP | `scripts/`, `docs/SOP/` |
| Deploy / CI | `docker-compose.yml`, `Caddyfile`, `.github/` |
| Vision / storyboard | `docs/VISION/` |

## Scope expansion

If the task needs a **forbidden** prefix (e.g. UI slice that must change `src/engine/`), **stop** and report — split slices or get steward exception; do not fold layers into one PR.

## BUILD handoff

Steward packets use [`BUILD_PACKET_TEMPLATE.md`](docs/SOP/BUILD_PACKET_TEMPLATE.md) with `LAYER`, `LAYER_PRESET`, `ALLOWED_PATHS`, `FORBIDDEN_PATHS`.
